com.guidewire.logging
Class LoggerCategory

java.lang.Object
  com.guidewire.logging.Logger
      com.guidewire.logging.LoggerCategory
All Implemented Interfaces:
gw.util.ILogger, java.lang.Comparable
public class LoggerCategory
extends Logger
implements java.lang.Comparable

A LoggerCategory represents a pre-defined type of a Logger. Categories are hierarchical in nature, e.g. a particular instance of a plugin should use a LoggerCategory that extends PLUGIN. Most of these LoggerCategories map to configurations in your "logging.properties" file, allowing you, for example, to map each category to a different log file.
